&lt;p&gt;Yes. If the operators are placed before the variable then the variable is changed before any other order of operations.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;$a=4;
$x=++$a + 6; will result in $x=11 and $a=5
$x=$a++ + 6; will result in $x=10 and $a=5
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When the operators are in front it takes precedence over all other operators. 
You can find a simple explanation at the following site as well:&lt;/p&gt;

