&lt;p&gt;and&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;if( $xmas = true ) :
                $showroom_img = "/media/gbu0/pagehead/showroom_xmas.jpg";
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In PHP, '=' is the assignment operator, used to assign value to a variable. What you need here is the comparison operator, '=='. For example :&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;if( $xmas == true ) :
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Or you could also do (it's pointed out in a comment already) :&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;if( $xmas ) :
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Rgarding priority, the if statements are going to be checked in the order you write them in your code. TO ensure that a condition gets the highest priority, that has to be checked first.&lt;/p&gt;
